ca.mcgill.hs.serv
Class LogFileUploaderService

java.lang.Object
  android.content.Context
      android.content.ContextWrapper
          android.app.Service
              ca.mcgill.hs.serv.LogFileUploaderService
All Implemented Interfaces:
android.content.ComponentCallbacks
public class LogFileUploaderService
extends android.app.Service

A new uploader service for the HSAndroid Application. When this service starts, it retrieves the list of saved files. Then, if an option is set, it will attempt to connect 3 times to a wifi connection. Afterwards, it will upload the files, recording error codes. Finally, it will toast the user to alert them of the success or failure of the operation. If the service was already started, then it will simply update the list of files and resume its operations.
